@startuml Activity_2_Automation
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam activityFontSize 14
skinparam arrowFontSize 13
skinparam swimlaneBorderThickness 2

title Activity Diagram 2 — Automation and AI Trigger Flow

|IoT Gateway|
start
:Receive sensor data from physical device\n(e.g. motion detected, temperature spike);
:Forward event to Device Management Service;

|Device Management Service|
:Update device state in cache;
:Persist event to central database;
:Notify Automation Engine of state change;

|Automation Engine|
:Evaluate all active automation rules\nagainst new device state;
if (Matching rule found?) then (yes)
    :Execute linked actions\n(e.g. turn on lights, lock doors);
    :Log automation event to database;
    :Notify Notification Service;
else (no)
    :No rule matched — log event;
endif
:Send usage event to AI / ML Service;

|AI / ML Service|
:Analyze event against historical\nbehavior patterns;
if (Pattern recognized?) then (yes)
    :Generate automation suggestion\n(e.g. suggest new routine);
    if (User has auto-apply enabled?) then (yes)
        :Apply suggestion automatically;
        :Log new rule to database;
    else (no)
        :Send suggestion to Notification Service;
    endif
else (no)
    :Continue learning — no action;
endif

|Notification Service|
:Determine notification type\n(confirmation / suggestion / alert);
:Dispatch push or email notification to user;

|Homeowner / Family Member|
:Receive notification;
if (Suggestion received?) then (yes)
    :Accept or reject automation suggestion;
    if (Accepted?) then (yes)
        :Automation Engine saves new rule;
    else (no)
        :Discard suggestion;
    endif
else (no)
    :Acknowledge alert or confirmation;
endif
stop

@enduml
